# Design Guidelines for Thrive Organization Web

## Core Design Principles

### 1. Modern & Clean Aesthetics
- **Minimalism First**: Remove unnecessary elements. Every component should have a clear purpose.
- **Generous White Space**: Use consistent spacing (4px base unit) to create breathing room and visual hierarchy.
- **Subtle Shadows**: Use soft, layered shadows (`shadow-xs`, `shadow-sm`) for depth without heaviness.
- **Rounded Corners**: Use consistent border radius (7-8px for inputs, 44px for buttons when appropriate) for modern feel.

### 2. Simplicity & Clarity
- **One Primary Action**: Each screen should have one clear primary action. Secondary actions should be visually de-emphasized.
- **Progressive Disclosure**: Show only essential information initially. Reveal details on demand.
- **Clear Visual Hierarchy**: Use font weights (400, 500, 600), sizes, and colors to guide user attention.
- **Consistent Patterns**: Reuse established patterns. Users should learn once, use everywhere.

### 3. Enterprise Application Excellence
- **Data Density**: Balance information density with readability. Enterprise users need efficiency.
- **Error Prevention**: Use inline validation, clear error messages, and helpful placeholders.
- **Keyboard Navigation**: Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible.
- **Loading States**: Always show loading indicators. Never leave users guessing.
- **Empty States**: Design helpful empty states that guide users to take action.

## Visual Design Standards

### Typography
- **Primary Font**: Poppins for body text (`font-poppins`)
- **Display Font**: Degular for headings (`font-degular`)
- **Font Sizes**: Use semantic sizes (text-sm, text-base, text-lg) - avoid arbitrary values
- **Font Weights**: 
  - Regular (400) for body text
  - Medium (500) for labels and emphasis
  - Semibold (600) for headings and important actions
- **Line Height**: Use default Tailwind line heights for optimal readability

### Color Palette

#### Primary Brand Colors
- **Primary Brand**: `#000093` - Main brand color for primary actions, CTAs, and key interactive elements
- **Primary Hover**: `#000080` - Darker shade for hover states on primary buttons
- **Primary Gradient**: `from-[#000080] to-[#3535AD]` - Gradient for selected/active states
- **Brand Light**: `#E0E0FF` - Light purple/blue for subtle backgrounds (e.g., action button backgrounds)
- **Sidebar Accent**: `#DBDBFF` and `#F1F1FF` - Sidebar navigation accent colors
- **Special Gradient**: `from-[#01F4C8] to-[#00A8FF]` - Cyan/teal to blue gradient for special actions (e.g., "Rewrite with AI", "Skip" buttons)
- **Icon Button Background**: `bg-[#E9F8FF]` with `border-[#BCE8FF]` - Light blue background for icon buttons

#### Text Colors
- **Primary Text**: `text-[#000000]` - Main body text, headings, and important content
- **Secondary Text**: `text-[#4D4D4D]` - Labels, placeholders, secondary information
- **Tertiary/Disabled**: `text-[#A4A4A4]` - Disabled states, less important text, icons
- **Brand Text**: `text-[#000093]` - Text using brand color for emphasis
- **Detail Labels**: `text-[#4E4E4E]` - Labels in detail views and information displays
- **Detail Values**: `text-[#000080]` - Values in detail views (darker brand color for emphasis)
- **Metadata Text**: `text-[#848484]` - Light gray for metadata, timestamps, and less important labels
- **Dark Gray**: `text-[#1E1E1E]` - Very dark gray for icons and subtle emphasis

#### Background Colors
- **Input Backgrounds**: `bg-[#F2F5F6]` - Standard background for form inputs and selects
- **Table Headers**: `bg-[#F3F3F3]` - Background for table headers and card sections
- **Card Backgrounds**: `bg-[#F3F3F3]` or `bg-[#F2F2F2]` - Subtle backgrounds for cards and containers
- **White**: `bg-white` - Primary container background
- **Light Brand Backgrounds**: `bg-[#E0E0FF]` - For action buttons and interactive elements
- **Detail Row Backgrounds**: `bg-[#F6F6F6]` - Background for detail rows in case views and information displays
- **Document Upload Area**: `bg-[#F9FAFB]` - Light background for file upload zones
- **Section Containers**: `bg-[#F2F5F6]` - Background for collapsible sections and form groups

#### Border Colors
- **Light Borders**: `border-[#EAEAEA]` - Subtle borders for cards and containers
- **Standard Borders**: `border-gray-300` - Default borders for inputs and dividers
- **Brand Borders**: `border-[#000093]` - Borders using brand color for emphasis
- **Section Borders**: `border-[#C1C1C1]` - Medium gray borders for section containers
- **Divider Borders**: `border-[#A7A7A7]` - Borders for accordion dividers and separators
- **Icon Button Borders**: `border-[#BCE8FF]` - Light blue borders for icon buttons

#### Interactive States
- **Focus Ring**: `focus:ring-[#00A8FF]/30` - Blue focus ring with 30% opacity for accessibility
- **Checkbox/Radio**: `text-[#000093]` - Brand color for selected checkboxes and radio buttons
- **Icons**: `text-blue-900` or `text-[#000093]` - Icon colors matching brand

#### Status Colors (Badges & Indicators)
- **Success**: Green gradients (`from-green-50 to-emerald-100` with `text-green-800`)
- **Pending**: Gray gradients (`from-slate-50 to-gray-100` with `text-slate-700`)
- **Ready**: Green gradients (`from-green-50 to-emerald-100` with `text-green-800`)
- **Waiting**: Blue gradients (`from-blue-50 to-indigo-100` with `text-blue-800`)
- **Info Required**: Purple gradients (`from-purple-50 to-violet-100` with `text-purple-700`)
- **Rejected**: Red gradients (`from-red-50 to-rose-100` with `text-red-800`)
- **Error**: `text-red-500` or `border-red-500` - For error states and validation

#### Usage Guidelines
- **Primary Actions**: Use `bg-[#000093]` with `hover:bg-[#000080]` for primary CTAs
- **Secondary Actions**: Use outline style with `border-[#000093]` and `text-[#000093]`
- **Text Hierarchy**: Use `#000000` → `#4D4D4D` → `#A4A4A4` for visual hierarchy
- **Consistency**: Always use the exact hex values (`#000093`, not approximations)
- **Accessibility**: Maintain WCAG AA contrast ratios (4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for UI components)

### Spacing System
- **Base Unit**: 4px (Tailwind's default)
- **Component Spacing**: 
  - `space-y-2` (8px) for tight groups
  - `space-y-5` (20px) for form sections
  - `gap-5` (20px) for grid layouts
- **Padding**: 
  - `p-3` (12px) for compact containers
  - `px-4 py-2` (16px/8px) for buttons
  - `p-6` (24px) for card padding
- **Margins**: Use consistent margins between sections (`mb-6`, `mt-8`)

### Component Design Patterns

#### Form Inputs
- **Height**: Standardize on `h-11` (44px) for all inputs - optimal touch target
- **Border Radius**: `rounded-[7.56px]` for inputs (consistent with existing pattern)
- **Focus States**: 
  - `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#00A8FF]/30` for primary focus
  - Always include focus-visible states for keyboard navigation
- **Icons**: Use lucide-react icons, size 16px (`size={16}`) for input icons
- **Placeholders**: Use descriptive, helpful placeholder text in `text-[#4D4D4D]`
- **Error States**: Red border (`border-red-500`) with error message below in `text-xs text-red-500`

#### Buttons
- **Primary Buttons**: 
  - `bg-[#000093]` with `hover:bg-[#000080]` or `hover:opacity-90`
  - `text-white` for text
  - `rounded-full` for pill-shaped buttons (common pattern)
  - Padding: `px-6 py-3` for standard, `px-2 py-1` for compact
- **Secondary/Outline Buttons**: 
  - `border border-gray-300` with `bg-white`
  - `hover:bg-gray-50` for hover state
  - `text-gray-700` for text
- **Brand Outline**: `border-[#000093]` with `text-[#000093]` for brand-colored outline buttons
- **Gradient Buttons**: `bg-gradient-to-b from-[#000080] to-[#3535AD]` for selected/active states
- **Action Buttons**: Use `bg-[#E0E0FF]` with `text-[#000093]` for subtle action buttons
- **States**: Always include hover, focus, active, and disabled states
- **Icons**: Icons should be size-4 (16px) and properly spaced with text
- **Loading**: Show loading spinner (`Loader2` with `animate-spin`) or disabled state during async operations
- **Rounded Corners**: Use `rounded-full` for pill buttons, `rounded-[44.3px]` for specific brand buttons

#### Dropdowns/Selects
- **Trigger**: Match input styling for consistency
- **Dropdown Menu**: 
  - `shadow-lg` for elevation
  - `max-h-[250px]` with scroll for long lists
  - Hide scrollbar visually (`[-ms-overflow-style:none] [&::-webkit-scrollbar]:hidden`)
- **Options**: Hover state with `hover:bg-gray-100`, padding `px-3 py-2`

#### Cards & Containers
- **Background**: White (`bg-white`) or light gray (`bg-[#F3F3F3]`) for card sections
- **Padding**: `p-3 sm:p-6` for responsive padding, `p-4` for compact cards
- **Border Radius**: 
  - `rounded-[30px]` or `rounded-[27px]` for large containers (tables, main cards, form sections)
  - `rounded-[20px]` for medium-sized containers (case detail sections)
  - `rounded-[13px]` for medium cards (mobile views)
  - `rounded-lg` (8px) or `rounded-md` (6px) for standard cards
  - `rounded-xl` (12px) for document upload areas
- **Borders**: `border-[1.18px] border-[#EAEAEA]` for subtle borders, `border-[#C1C1C1]` for section containers
- **Shadow**: Use `shadow-sm` or `shadow-xs` for subtle elevation, or rely on borders

#### Action Buttons & Links
- **Action Button Style**: 
  - Background: `bg-[#E0E0FF]` (light brand color)
  - Icon: `text-[#000093]` 
  - Size: `h-[30px] w-[40px]` for compact actions
  - Shape: `rounded-full`
  - Hover: `hover:opacity-80`
- **Link Buttons**: Use brand color `text-[#000093]` with hover states
- **Special Action Buttons**: 
  - Gradient: `bg-gradient-to-l from-[#01F4C8] to-[#00A8FF]` for special actions (Skip, AI features)
  - Text: `text-white` on gradient backgrounds
  - Size: `h-[45px]` with appropriate width
- **Icon Buttons**: 
  - Background: `bg-[#E9F8FF]` with `border-[#BCE8FF]`
  - Icon color: `text-[#000093]`
  - Size: `h-[32px] w-[32px]` or `h-[38px] w-[38px]` for larger icons
  - Shape: `rounded-full`

#### Headings & Typography Scale
- **Page Titles**: `text-[32px] sm:text-[36px] md:text-[40px] font-semibold text-[#000000]`
- **Section Headings**: `text-lg font-semibold text-[#000000]` or `text-2xl font-semibold text-[#000093]`
- **Table Headers**: `text-[15px]` or `text-sm font-semibold text-[#000000]`
- **Body Text**: `text-[16px]` or `text-sm` with `text-[#4D4D4D]` or `text-[#000000]`
- **Small Text**: `text-[12px]` or `text-xs` for labels and metadata

## User Experience Principles

### 1. Feedback & Responsiveness
- **Immediate Feedback**: Show loading states, success messages, and errors immediately
- **Micro-interactions**: Subtle transitions (`transition-all`) for state changes
- **Optimistic Updates**: Update UI optimistically when possible, rollback on error

### 2. Navigation & Flow
- **Breadcrumbs**: Use breadcrumbs for deep navigation hierarchies
- **Back Buttons**: Provide clear back navigation, especially in multi-step flows
- **Progressive Forms**: Break long forms into logical steps with clear progress indicators

### 3. Data Display
- **Tables**: 
  - Header background: `bg-[#F3F3F3]` with `text-[#000000]`
  - Header styling: `font-poppins text-[15px]` or `text-sm font-semibold`
  - Row background: `bg-white` with `border-b` for separation
  - Cell text: `text-[#4D4D4D]` for data, `text-[#000000]` for emphasis
  - Container: `rounded-[27px] border-[1.18px] border-[#EAEAEA] bg-white p-3 sm:p-6`
  - Sortable columns: Use `text-[#000093]` for sort indicators when active
- **Mobile Card View**: 
  - Card background: `bg-[#F3F3F3]`
  - Rounded corners: `rounded-[13px]`
  - Label text: `text-[12px] text-[#4D4D4D]`
  - Value text: `text-[14px] text-black`
- **Lists**: Use consistent list patterns with clear hierarchy
- **Empty States**: Design helpful empty states with clear CTAs
- **Loading Skeletons**: Use skeleton loaders that match the content structure

### 4. Error Handling
- **Inline Validation**: Validate on blur, show errors below fields
- **Error Messages**: Use clear, actionable error messages (not technical jargon)
- **Error Placement**: Show errors near the relevant field, not at the top
- **Success Feedback**: Confirm successful actions with toast notifications or inline messages

## Accessibility (A11y) Standards

### Keyboard Navigation
- **Tab Order**: Logical tab order following visual flow
- **Focus Indicators**: Visible focus rings (`focus-visible:ring-2`)
- **Skip Links**: Provide skip links for main content areas
- **Keyboard Shortcuts**: Document and support common shortcuts

### Screen Readers
- **Semantic HTML**: Use proper HTML elements (button, nav, main, etc.)
- **ARIA Labels**: Add aria-labels for icon-only buttons and complex components
- **Form Labels**: Always associate labels with inputs using `htmlFor` and `id`
- **Required Fields**: Use `required` attribute and visual indicator (`*`)

### Visual Accessibility
- **Color Contrast**: Maintain WCAG AA standards (4.5:1 for text)
- **Don't Rely on Color**: Use icons, text, or patterns in addition to color
- **Text Size**: Ensure text is readable (minimum 14px for body text)
- **Touch Targets**: Minimum 44x44px for interactive elements

## Performance & Optimization

### Loading Performance
- **Code Splitting**: Use Next.js dynamic imports for heavy components
- **Image Optimization**: Use Next.js Image component with proper sizing
- **Lazy Loading**: Lazy load below-the-fold content and modals
- **Skeleton Screens**: Show skeleton loaders instead of blank screens

### Runtime Performance
- **Debounce Inputs**: Debounce search and filter inputs (300ms)
- **Virtual Scrolling**: Use virtual scrolling for long lists (100+ items)
- **Memoization**: Use React.memo, useMemo, useCallback appropriately
- **Bundle Size**: Monitor and optimize bundle size

## Enterprise-Specific Considerations

### Data Management
- **Bulk Actions**: Provide bulk selection and actions for efficiency
- **Filters**: Advanced filtering with clear, persistent filter states
- **Sorting**: Multi-column sorting with clear indicators
- **Pagination**: Consistent pagination patterns with page size options

### Security & Permissions
- **Permission-Based UI**: Hide/disable features based on user permissions
- **Sensitive Actions**: Require confirmation for destructive actions
- **Audit Trail**: Show who did what and when (if applicable)

### Scalability
- **Responsive Design**: Mobile-first approach, ensure desktop optimization
- **Tablet Support**: Ensure good experience on tablet devices
- **Print Styles**: Consider print-friendly layouts for reports

## Code Quality Standards

### Component Structure
- **TypeScript**: Use TypeScript for all components with proper types
- **Props Interface**: Define clear prop interfaces with JSDoc comments
- **Default Props**: Provide sensible defaults for optional props
- **Composition**: Prefer composition over complex prop drilling

### Styling
- **Tailwind Classes**: Use Tailwind utility classes, avoid inline styles
- **Custom Classes**: Extract repeated patterns into reusable classes
- **Consistent Naming**: Use consistent class naming patterns
- **Responsive**: Mobile-first responsive design with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints

### State Management
- **React Hook Form**: Use React Hook Form for all forms
- **Zod Validation**: Use Zod schemas for form validation
- **Server State**: Use appropriate data fetching patterns (Server Components when possible)
- **Client State**: Use React state or Zustand for client-only state

# Page Guidelines

## Page Structure
- Use **separate pages** for **Create** and **Edit** forms.
- Display the **page title and primary create action (icon/button)** on the **same horizontal row**.
- Align **search and filter controls consistently** within the page header or action area

## Loading & Empty States
- On initial page load:
  - Always render the **page title, primary actions, search, filters, and table headers** immediately.
  - Display a **loader only within the table content area**, not the entire page.
- If no records are available:
  - Show a **clear empty state message** within the table content area.
  - Include guidance or a call-to-action when appropriate (e.g., “Create your first item”).

## Table Behavior
- All table columns **must support sorting** unless explicitly exempted.
- Sorting state should be **visually indicated** and **persist across interactions** where applicable.

## Filters & Search
- Filters must be **clearly visible and accessible**.
- Provide a **Clear Filters** action that:
  - Resets all filters and search inputs.
  - Restores the default table state.

## Actions
- Clearly define and document:
  - **Primary actions** (e.g., Create).
  - **Row-level actions** (e.g., Edit, Delete).
  - **Bulk actions**, if supported.
- Group secondary or destructive actions under an **ellipsis (overflow) menu** when space is constrained.

## Non-Goals
- These guidelines do not define pagination strategy, authorization rules, or backend sorting behavior.

# Additional Critical Guidelines to Add

## 1. Interaction States Must Be Fully Defined
- Every interactive component must define: **default**, **hover**, **active/pressed**, **focus-visible**, **disabled**, **loading**.
- Disabled elements must provide a **reason** when appropriate (tooltip/help text), especially when permission-based.

## 2. Confirmation, Undo, and Destructive Actions
- Destructive actions (e.g., **Delete**, **Remove**, **Revoke**, **Archive**) must require **confirmation**.
- Prefer **Undo** patterns for reversible actions (e.g., toast with “Undo”) over modal confirmations where possible.
- Clearly distinguish destructive actions via:
  - **Placement** (de-prioritized)
  - **Labeling** (“Delete” not “Remove” if permanent)
  - **Styling** (danger treatment)

## 3. Global Feedback Standards
- Standardize system feedback:
  - **Toasts** for non-blocking confirmations
  - **Inline messages** for form validation and field errors
  - **Banners** for persistent/global issues (permission changes, outages, maintenance)
- Success states must be **explicit** (e.g., “Saved” with timestamp if relevant).

## 4. Error Handling and Recovery
- Error messages must be:
  - **Actionable** (e.g., “Try again”, “Check your permissions”, “Contact support”)
  - **Non-technical** (avoid exposing raw API errors)
- Provide recovery patterns:
  - **Retry** for transient failures
  - **Re-authenticate** for auth/session issues
  - **Fallback content** for partial page failures


## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### Visual Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Inconsistent spacing and sizing
- ❌ Too many colors or competing visual elements
- ❌ Dense, cluttered layouts without breathing room
- ❌ Inconsistent button styles and sizes
- ❌ Poor contrast ratios
- ❌ Missing loading states

### UX Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Dead-end pages without navigation
- ❌ Forms without validation feedback
- ❌ Destructive actions without confirmation
- ❌ No error handling or unclear error messages
- ❌ Hidden or unclear primary actions
- ❌ Inconsistent navigation patterns

### Code Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Inline styles instead of Tailwind classes
- ❌ Missing TypeScript types
- ❌ Prop drilling instead of composition
- ❌ Unnecessary re-renders
- ❌ Hardcoded values instead of constants

## Quick Reference Checklist

When creating a new component or page, ensure:
- [ ] Consistent spacing using Tailwind spacing scale
- [ ] Proper TypeScript types defined
- [ ] Accessible (keyboard navigation, ARIA labels, focus states)
- [ ] Responsive design (mobile-first)
- [ ] Loading and error states handled
- [ ] Consistent with existing design patterns
- [ ] Clear visual hierarchy
- [ ] WCAG AA contrast ratios
- [ ] Proper form validation with React Hook Form
- [ ] Helpful error messages
- [ ] Optimized performance (memoization, lazy loading if needed)

